Amazon.com Inc. (AMZN) is reportedly planning to play global catchup with Netflix Inc. (NFLX). Amazon is preparing to launch its streaming video service into about 200 countries, according to The Wall Street Journal (http://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-gearing-up-for-global-launch-of-streaming-video-service-1479414380), citing sources. The Journal reported the news on Thursday following a YouTube video that hinted at the rollout. Shares of Amazon were up more than 1% in afternoon trade and are up nearly 12% in the year to date, while the S&P 500 Index is up nearly 7%.
-Trey Williams;
 1542ET

Amazon.com Inc. (AMZN) is reportedly planning to play global catchup with Netflix Inc. (NFLX). Amazon is preparing to launch its streaming video service into about 200 countries, according to The Wall Street Journal (http://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-gearing-up-for-global-launch-of-streaming-video-service-1479414380), citing sources. The Journal reported the news on Thursday following a YouTube video that hinted at the rollout. Netflix stock dropped as much as 1.4% to an intraday low of $113.56 minutes after The Journal broke the news, before paring the losses.Shares of Amazon were up more than 1% in afternoon trade and are up nearly 12% in the year to date, while the S&P 500 Index is up nearly 7%.
-Trey Williams;
